The paper deals with the compression of light field images for interactive rendering, which is a topic that falls under computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of phase shifted motion compensation techniques, which is a signal processing technique (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the compression rate and PSNR, which are metrics commonly used in information theory (cs.IT).
